HEADWORD: Thunderer
<hw>Thun"der*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who thunders;
-- used especially as a translation of L. <xex>tonans</xex>, an epithet
applied by the Romans to several of their gods, esp. to
<persfn>Jupiter</persfn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That dreadful oath which binds the <qex>Thunderer</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thunderfish</ent>⟦br⟧
